# Retailer Integration Framework

## Overview

Retailer integrations enable wholesale organizations to exchange order, shipment, and financial data with external partners automatically. These integrations allow purchase orders, inventory updates, shipment notifications, and invoices to move between systems without manual intervention.

Retail integrations are typically managed through EDI platforms, retailer portals, or direct API connections.

---

## Integration Channels

Wholesale organizations commonly integrate with retail partners through several channels:

• Electronic Data Interchange (EDI)  
• retailer vendor portals  
• wholesale order management platforms  
• API integrations  
• marketplace integration platforms  

Each integration channel may require different configuration and monitoring processes.

---

## Common Integration Platforms

Examples of platforms used to connect wholesale systems with retailers include:

• SPS Commerce  
• CommerceHub  
• TrueCommerce  
• Retailer-specific portals  
• Marketplace integration platforms  

These systems help standardize communication between different enterprise systems.

---

## Typical Retail EDI Transactions

Retail integrations usually rely on standardized EDI transaction sets.

Common transactions include:

| EDI Code | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| 850 | Purchase Order |
| 855 | Purchase Order Acknowledgement |
| 856 | Advance Ship Notice |
| 810 | Invoice |

These transactions automate order and shipment communication between organizations.

---

## Integration Lifecycle

Retail integrations typically follow a structured implementation lifecycle.

1. Retail partner onboarding  
2. System mapping configuration  
3. EDI testing and validation  
4. Production activation  
5. Ongoing monitoring and support  

Testing is critical to ensure orders transmit correctly between systems.

---

## Integration Ownership

Retail integrations often involve coordination between multiple teams:

• operations teams  
• IT or systems teams  
• integration platform providers  
• retailer technical contacts  
• finance teams for invoice validation  

Clear ownership ensures integrations remain stable and reliable.

---

## Integration Monitoring

Operations teams should monitor integrations regularly to ensure:

• purchase orders are received successfully  
• shipment notifications transmit correctly  
• invoice data matches system records  
• integration errors are resolved quickly  

Regular monitoring prevents operational disruption.

---

## Final Note

Reliable retailer integrations are critical to modern wholesale operations. When integrations function correctly, organizations can process orders faster, reduce manual errors, and maintain consistent communication with retail partners.
